title: 2 escape injury after small plane crashes in East Texas
text:
WASKOM, Texas (AP) - Two people have escaped injury after a small plane crashed before dawn in East Texas about 20 miles west of Shreveport, Louisiana.
Authorities tell the Marshall News Messenger ( http://bit.ly/1G1dLqA ) the aircraft went down north of Waskom about 4 a.m. Monday when it apparently ran out of fuel.
The plane had left Harrison County Airport near Marshall, flew to adjacent Gregg County and was headed back to Marshall when it crashed.
The Texas Department of Public Safety is investigating.
Information from: Marshall News Messenger, http://www.coxnews.com/marshall.htm
